<p>all my issue is specified in the title. I downloaded <a href="http://ianlunn.github.io/Hover/" rel="nofollow">a hover css transition package</a>. One of his class is called "hvr-sink".This css transition class on navbar make redirection link not clickable but only on smartphone. That's work fine for other devices. </p>  <p>EDIT: after having searching a long time I note that only my phone doesn't support the hover. I'm running with an Iphone 4S. 2 friends' mobiles work well.</p>  <p>You can see the <a href="http://remake.medieval-fields.com/content/" rel="nofollow">site there</a>. Test the navigation bar on computer then on smartphone. The hover sink is implemented on each list element. I really don't understand why that doesn't work on smartphone only.</p>  <p>My first website works well with "same transition in the navbar". medieval-fields.com/accueil/</p>  <p>CSS used for the class hvr-sink :</p>  <pre><code> .navbar-default .navbar-nav &gt; li &gt; a:hover,  .navbar-default .navbar-nav &gt; li &gt; a:focus {      color: #2980b9 !important;     background-color: transparent;     font-family: exo;   }   .navbar-nav &gt; li &gt; a, .navbar-brand {     height: 80px;     padding-bottom: 0 !important;     font-size: 18px;   }   .hvr-sink {   display: inline-block;   vertical-align: middle;   -webkit-transform: translateZ(0);   transform: translateZ(0);   box-shadow: 0 0 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);   -webkit-backface-visibility: hidden;   backface-visibility: hidden;   -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;   -webkit-transition-duration: 0.3s;   transition-duration: 0.3s;   -webkit-transition-property: transform;   transition-property: transform;   -webkit-transition-timing-function: ease-out;   transition-timing-function: ease-out; } .hvr-sink:hover, .hvr-sink:focus, .hvr-sink:active {   -webkit-transform: translateY(8px);   transform: translateY(8px); } </code></pre>  <p>navbar link html code for example :</p>  <p><code>&lt;li class='hvr-sink'&gt;&lt;a href="teamspeak.php"&gt;Teamspeak&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</code></p>  <p>Edit : I'm using bootstrap</p>  <p>Thanks for reading. Regards,</p>